  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6583 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6500 (-4.5B) and positive gamma zone at 6600 (+3.5B), dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but poised for directional flow. The PIN regime and recent GEX surge indicate dealers will aggressively buy any dip toward 6500 (creating amplified bounces) while selling rallies above 6600 (capping upside). Key inflection points are 6500 downside magnet where dealer buying accelerates and 6600 resistance where dealer selling kicks in.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pulled between 6500-6600 with choppy action until one of these major gamma walls breaks.",
